# Poll

## Poll List

This endpoint generates a list of polls. 

> The API returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "group_id": 1,
      "group_name": "Management",
      "group_image": "https://example.com/media/image.png",
      "created_by": 1,
      "hide_poll_users": true,
      "title": "Question",
      "description": "Informationaboutthequestion",
      "poll_type": 0,
      "public": false,
      "tag": 1,
      "tag_name": "defaulttag",
      "start_date": ***,
      "proposal_end_date": ***,
      "prediction_end_date": ***,
      "delegate_vote_end_date": ***,
      "end_date": ***,
      "finished": false,
      "result": false,
      "participants": 2,
      "dynamic": false
    }, ...
  ]
}
```

### HTTP Request

`GET <%= config[:endpoint] %>/group/<group_id>/poll/list`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter                   | Notes                                          |
|-----------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| `id` *int*                  |                                                |
| `title` *str*               |                                                |
| `title__icontains` *str*    |                                                |
| `poll_type` *int*           | Polls can be either 0 ranking or 1 for-against |
| `tag` *int*                 |                                                |
| `tag_name` *str*            |                                                |
| `tag_name__icontains` *str* |                                                |
| `finished` *bool*           |                                                |


